Class AgentDelegate

    • Method Detail

      • getTransactionDemarcator

        public static ITransactionDemarcator getTransactionDemarcator()
        Gets the handle to the transaction demarcator API. Returns null if the Java agent is not initialized in the current JVM (e.g. -javaagent option is not added to the JVM startup command or agent failed to initialize). Note that the transaction demarcator object could change after this class is initialized; therefore, we must get a fresh copy each time.
        Returns:
        an implementation of ITransactionDemarcator interface
        See Also:
        ITransactionDemarcator
